A rectangular piece of fabric and a triangular piece of fabric are sewn together to make a banner. The area of the triangular piece of fabric is $24$ square inches. Find the total area of the banner.

\begin{tikzpicture}
% Rectangle
\draw (0,0) -- (2.5,0) -- (2.5,2) -- (0,2) -- cycle;
% Triangle on top
\draw (0,2) -- (1.25,3) -- (2.5,2);
% Labels
\node[above left] at (0,2) {6 in};
\node[below] at (1.25,0) {9 in};
\end{tikzpicture}

The total area of the banner is \underline{\hspace{1cm}} square inches.
